4. What is the duration of the medical program at the Medical University of Warsaw?
The duration of the medical program at the Medical University of Warsaw varies depending on the specific program and curriculum. Generally, undergraduate medical programs typically span six years, including both pre-clinical and clinical training. Graduate and postgraduate programs may have different durations depending on the specialization and level of study medicine in Warsaw. Our consultants at Qadri International Educational Consultants in UAE can provide information on the duration of the medical programs offered at the university.

5. Can international students work part-time while studying medicine at the Medical University of Warsaw?
International students studying medicine at the Medical University of Warsaw may be eligible to work part-time during their studies, subject to certain regulations and restrictions. The university's international student office can provide information and guidance on the employment opportunities available to students, as well as any visa requirements or limitations.
